node.text:
Today at Noon, we are happy to introduce, dHop35 (8.5% DIPA) $20 per 4-pk, no limit. We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Pennsylvania, Kentucky, Nebraska, and Virginia.

Our latest iteration in our dHop series tries an experimental dry hop technique for the first time to enhance our signature EQJuice profile along with the energy treatment. dHop 35 follows the success of dHop 34 with flaked oats and flaked wheat, an Idaho7 and mosaic WP, and a huge dry hop of 100% citra that undergoes the dHop34 hopping technique in addition to EQ’s energy treatment. dHop 35 pours a very vibrant yellow, releasing bright tropical notes of rainbow melon, bright citrus, mango, pineapple, and peach with a huge #🌈🍈 #EQjuice finish.

node.text:
Today at Noon, we are happy to introduce, Einstein’s Decadence (8.0% DIPA) $22 per 4-pk, no limit. We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Pennsylvania, Kentucky, Nebraska, and Virginia.

Our newest play on one of Einstein’s favorite deserts takes a decadent turn. Einstein’s Decadence is our newest version of one of his favorite desserts, Orange Sticky Cake. We took a heavily hopped Citra forward DIPA, added more of our favorite hops, an indulgent dose of Florida navel orange zest, Madagascar Vanilla, and Marshmallows. This dessert themed beer has bright notes and flavors of tropical orange slices and assorted citrus, vanilla funfetti cake, and sweet creamy marshmallow frosting.

node.text:
This Wednesday, 7/28/21 at 9am on Eventbrite and this Saturday, 7/31/21 at 11am at Retail, we will sell Barrel Aged Special Relativity 1- Batch 3 (14% ABV Imperial Stout) $22 per 500 ML bottle. Limit 1 bottle per person. No proxies. Please add Eventbrite confirmation to Pickup or Delivery orders when checking out on our website. No Minimum order for shipping bottles to NY, PA, D.C, OH, VT, ND, NV, NH, KY. NE or VA but please keep in mind the flat rate is in place based on your location. Claim by 8/4/21 and please add Eventbrite order number while checking out on our website. 

During a Friday afternoon sensory panel several weeks ago, we tasted liquid from many barrels. One sip and we all immediately agreed that this single barrel had become the latest BASR1. Aged in a single select Weller barrel for just over 14 months and bottled absent of any of adjuncts, we aimed to show this stellar barrel off and let its unique characteristics shine. Pouring pitch black with a tan head, aromas of oaky bourbon filled chocolate truffles lead into flavors of rich bakers chocolate, freshly ground coffee, dark fruits, tobacco, brownie batter, and leather. These sensory experiences come together in an extremely viscous body with a smooth bourbon note accompanied by a complex vanilla and caramel silk like finish. This beer is the culmination of a magical base and a truly special barrel.

Today at Noon, we will sell Straight Outta the South Street Lab (10% TIPA) at $22 per 4-pk, no limit. We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Pennsylvania, Kentucky, Nebraska, and Virginia.
New block, new lab! Straight Outta The South Street Lab builds off of our SOTL grain bill and our hand selected Citra hop bill and experiments with our newest processes made possible by our South Street Setup to bring you even more of that #🌈🍈 EQJuice… South Street Style. We get bright notes of rainbow melon, peach, tropical orange juice, creamy, mango smoothie, and dank grass. It’s resinous and chewy with an escalating brightness and a strong #EQJuice finish.

Today at Noon, we will sell, Fluctuating Fruits: Pink Guava/Plum (8.1 % ABV Fruited DIPA) at $22 per 4pk. No Limit. We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Pennsylvania, Kentucky, Nebraska, and Virginia.

Fluctuating Fruits is back today with our newest combination, Pink Guava and Plum. We started off with our Fluctuation base, dry hopped it with Citra and Galaxy before adding 2200 lbs of Pink Guava and Plum. Pouring a deep milky orange plum color, aromas of citrus and tropical fruit lead into flavors on Tang juice drink, ripe summer plums and a balanced guava pop with a touch of complex coconut all wrapped in a creamy finish.

node.text:
Today at 12 PM, we will sell Hydrophilic (8.5% DIPA) at $ 20 per 4-PK, no limit. We will have this available at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Pennsylvania, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Kentucky, Nebraska, and Virginia! (Please follow individual State limits for delivery)
Hydrophilic literally means “water love”. A hydrophilic molecule has more favorable thermodynamic interactions with polar solvents vs non polar solvents, which means yummy compounds will stay in the beer verses sorbing and settling with yeast or volatizing out of the fermentor during fermentation. This beer utilizes a new product from Yakima Chief Hops, which is a Cryo Survivables hop blend. We used this blend in the whirlpool which allows the yummy hop compounds to end up in your glass instead of making great tasting yeast or the refreshing the brewery air.
Starting off with flaked oats and wheat we used YCH cyro survivables hop blend and then dry hopped with Citra and Rakau. Pouring a hazy and straw yellow we get aromas of citrus, passionfruit, and melon with deep flavors of candied orange, passionfruit, cantaloupe, peach, apricot, and a touch of berry packed into a luscious mouthfeel with a creamy and explosive #🌈🍈 #EQjuice finish.
